cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR 

The paper deals with the problem of sim2real transfer learning for 3D pose estimation, which is a topic that falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and robotics (cs.RO). The paper also discusses the use of neural networks (cs.LG) and motion cues (cs.AI) to bridge the sim2real gap. Finally, the evaluation is done on a dataset (3D Poses in the Wild) that is related to graphics (cs.GR).
